  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "**BUG REPORT**:\r\n\r\n**Kubernetes version latest master**:\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n- **Ubuntu 16.04 LTS, Linux 4.2.0-42-generic**:\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\nThe `flock.Acquire()` doesn't provide mutual exclusion. Two processes can both grab the same flock at the same time.\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\nOnly one process should be able to grab the flock.\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it** (as minimally and precisely as possible):\r\n\r\n```shell\r\ncat testflock.go\r\npackage main\r\n\r\nimport (\r\n\t\"fmt\"\r\n\t\"time\"\r\n\r\n\t\"k8s.io/kubernetes/pkg/util/flock\"\r\n)\r\n\r\nfunc main() {\r\n\tif err := flock.Acquire(\"/tmp/foo.lock\"); err != nil {\r\n\t\tfmt.Println(\"error:\", err)\r\n\t\treturn\r\n\t}\r\n\r\n\tfmt.Println(\"acquired\")\r\n\r\n\ttime.Sleep(time.Hour)\r\n}\r\n\r\ngo build testflock.go; ./testflock\r\nacquired\r\n\r\n# open another terminal and run\r\n./testflock\r\nacquired\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Anything else we need to know**:\r\n\r\nAlthough the flock doesn't work, the [watchForLockfileContention()](https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/v1.7.0-alpha.0/cmd/kubelet/app/server.go#L324) does work. Since we _usually_ specify `--exit-on-lock-contention` together with `--lock-file`, so the 1st process will exit anyway.\r\nHowever we still need to fix the flock..\r\n",
